Calculation of the estimate of construction objects in the Russian Federation will take place in a new way
The Federal Antitrust Service takes special control of the issues of pricing, regulation of the construction industry, as well as the problems of connection to the networks.
The FAS has established an expert council for the development of competition in the construction sector.
At his meeting, Vadim Solovyev, head of the control department of residential, construction and natural resources of FAS, said that "today's calculation of the estimate of construction objects is absolutely incomprehensible".
The regulatory framework makes pricing opaque and can lead to an unreasonable construction price, the FAS believes.
And offer the cost of construction of state-owned objects at the design stage to determine on the basis of market prices of constructive solutions instead of today’s estimated norms and unit prices for technological operations.
These proposals have been included in the road map and are currently being considered by the Ministry of Foreign Affairs.
"The replacement of traditional estimate documentation in construction with calculations of constructive elements should lead to less corruption in the industry," Vadim Solovyev explained.
After all, now in the waste every bolt and nut is calculated, and it is not always possible to check everything, so sometimes in the documentation dishonest construction companies can bury "whole tractors".
I agree with the FAS.
"The first developments on the transition to the calculation of value on constructive elements already exist: methods for calculating prices on constructive solutions, compiling estimates on these indicators have been developed," said Elena Zhukova, Head of the Department of Urban Development and Architecture of the Ministry of Architecture.
The field of road construction was selected as a pilot.
However, experts believe that the problem is much more serious.
According to the head of the construction company "Profi-Invest" Anatoly Demyanko, the estimated regulations are obsolete for a long time, but another mechanism for business has not yet been proposed.
"As for the proposed calculations on the constructive elements, in practice, this is difficult to implement, since when building buildings are often used completely different technologies," - he believes.
It is no secret that the construction market is developing largely thanks to the state order.
According to the Chairman of the Board of NP "Expert Community of Professionals of the State Order" Ekaterina Lezina, today the state is the most solvent customer.
Vladimir Malakhov, deputy director of engineering of the industrial center of capital construction Rosatom, drew attention to the fact that today the market is conditionally divided into companies that have access to a portfolio of contracts, and companies that own monopolistic competencies and do not allow competitors in this field.
He believes that the creation of a transparent market is possible only if access to contracts is protected as much as possible from the influence of someone else.
At the expert council, it was proposed to form a system of state orders in such a way that the same contractor is not entitled to receive more than one contract for the amount of more than 1 billion rubles or several contracts for the amount of more than 1 billion rubles.
In the mindset, it is believed that this approach should be evaluated in terms of the impact on business, as well as the effectiveness of construction management.
As Elena Zhukova explained, in this case it will be necessary to appoint the customer with the functions of a general contractor, which will lead to an increase in the number of staff of the customer and budgetary expenses for its maintenance.
At the same time, the customer’s specialists will have to have the knowledge to assess the quality of the works performed by the contracting organizations, as well as their safety.
Often, in such a breakdown, it will be necessary to determine who will be responsible for the safety of the facility as a whole.
In addition, this approach may result in the outflow of highly qualified public procurement participants due to a lack of interest in receiving a public order for incomplete work and a small amount of contract.
Deputy head of the expert and consulting center of the Institute of Procurement Alexander Yevstaschenkov believes that now the procedure of the state order has turned into a business game at the attention of the contractor.
And gave an example: "the participant when filling in the application must indicate "concrete indicators" without specifying the words: "or equivalent", "must be", "from", "more", "less", "analogue", "or", "type", "of the same type", "not below", "below", "below", "can't", "can't", "can't", "more", "can't", "can't", "more", "can'"
Thus, customers often abuse their right to set requirements for the content of the application submitted by contracting entities.
Another problem 44-FZ, according to Yevstaschenkov, was the need to assess the quality of work at the stage of application through the "paper" offer of the participant.
Considering the application of the participant, it is realistic to evaluate only the qualification of the contractor, but not the quality of the work, which has not even begun to be carried out, - the expert believes.
The quality of the work can only be assessed when it is received.
The expert council was also proposed to move the margin income from the top to the bottom to eliminate intermediate contractors.
The Chairman of the Expert Council, the State Secretary, Deputy Head of FAS Andrey Tsarikovsky believes that this should not be done, since the general contractor should be responsible for the order.
And otherwise it will turn out, as in the famous reprise of Arkady Raikin "Atelier": "Is there a claim to the buttons?".
Israeli children return to school after the war in Gaza
Thousands of Israeli children in areas near the Gaza Strip went back to school on Monday after spending the summer in bomb shelters when rockets and landmines fell on their settlements during the 50-day war between Israel and Hamas, while schools in the Gaza Strip remained closed.
The beginning of schooling brought a sense of joy and excitement to the rocket-stricken settlements of southern Israel, but the traces of fighting remained fresh.
