No matter what equipment you use, there are a few rules you need to follow in order to get the best results.
Inspect your equipment.
Even if you have a waterproof camera, make sure the camera battery and other compartments are tightly closed.
Also, set up your camera for the type of photos or videos you will be shooting.
Some cameras have shooting modes or object type that optimize exposure for darkened underwater conditions.
And before you jump into the water, figure out how deep your equipment can sink.
Some cameras are designed for only 5 feet, others - 50 or 60 feet.
Check out our buyer’s guide and digital camera ratings for both traditional and waterproof models.
