Make a few frames.
Also, if your camera has a serial shooting mode that shoots multiple frames with slightly different exposure settings, take advantage of it.
Stay on the surface.
The amount of light decreases significantly the deeper you dive underwater.
If possible, stay close to the surface when shooting in the pool, river, or ocean.
This will also allow you to pass on more colors in the photos; the deeper you go, the less colors you will see.
Navigate closer to the shooting objects.
