The Ministry of Economic Development wants to accelerate the growth of the electric car market
This week, the Ministry of Economic Development will introduce to the government a comprehensive plan for the development of environmentally friendly transport in Russia, said Deputy Director of the Department of the Ministry Oleg Pluzhnikov at a round table held by "Vedomosti" at the Moscow Motor Show - 2014.
The plan was drafted by the government, one of the main objectives is to reduce greenhouse gas emissions.
It is expected that the document will be adopted at the end of September - beginning of October, says Pluzhnikov, the proposed measures concerning electric vehicles and hybrids - a plan for the development of vehicles on gas-powered fuel in Russia already exists.
The plan (a copy is available from Vedomosti) is for 2014-2017.
The criteria for evaluating electric and hybrid transport are to be developed and how to stimulate the use and production of environmentally friendly vehicles.
A report to the government, which will describe tax and customs support measures for electric vehicles, will be prepared by December 2014; a scheme of preferential lending and preferential leasing will appear by April 2015; and proposals for lowering the price of cars, stimulating localization and creating service infrastructure will be developed.
In 2014-2015, it is planned to make changes to the regulatory acts to facilitate the conditions for the construction of charging infrastructure (on parking lots, gas stations, etc.).
In addition, federal officials intend to formulate proposals for regional authorities during 2015 to also encourage the use of environmentally friendly transport - in the form of giving it an advantage in traffic and parking, for example; and by February 2016 - and proposals to expand public procurement of such transport.
Finally, by October 2014, the Ministry of Economic Development will include in the list of indicators of evaluation of the activities of regional authorities criteria reflecting the effectiveness of support for the production of environmentally friendly transport, the development of charging infrastructure.
The market for electric vehicles in Russia is still being formed – in 2013, about 100 electric vehicles were sold throughout the country.
At the beginning of 2014, the import duty on electric cars was zeroed, so sales will be about 500 pieces, predicts Mitsubishi Motors CEO in Russia Andrey Pankov.
But the five-fold increase does not make electric cars any noticeable: in 2013, according to the Association of European Business, 2.78 million cars and light commercial vehicles were sold in Russia.
Only Mitsubishi Motors imports electric vehicles into Russia.
Renault is preparing to start importing - the company focuses primarily on corporate customers, says the director of strategic planning and partnerships of Renault in Russia, Nicolas Remis.
Most of the other manufacturers of electric transport have taken a waiting position in relation to Russia.
The development of electric vehicles has Russian manufacturers - "", GAZ, "", but the output is miserable.
For example, in January - July 2014, according to "ASM-holding", "AvtoVAZ" produced 30 electric vehicles.
Demand is low due to the cost of electric vehicles, admits the director of "AvtoVAZ" on engineering Sergey Amanov, without the state support of the breakthrough in this segment will not be.
The development of the Russian market of electric vehicles in addition to the cost of cars (the electric cars sold in Russia, on average twice as expensive as analogues with internal combustion engines) restrains the underdevelopment of the charging infrastructure (tanks - units), exhales the CEO of "Avtostarkov"
Due to the cost and low rates of cost reduction, electric cars in the next 3-4 years will remain a niche segment of the Russian market, forecasts the editor-in-chief of "Avtorev" Mikhail Podorozhansky, Tselikov agrees with him.
Automakers, on the other hand, say that some models of electric vehicles are already close to the cost of conventional ones.
The Russian electric vehicle market has good prospects, the main thing is to give confidence to consumers that "e-mobility" is real; this, in particular, will be facilitated by the emergence of new charging stations, stresses the president of the BMW Group in Russia Wolfgang Slimme.
Such infrastructure projects are implemented, for example, by the state company "Rossetti": in Moscow, several stations have been built, soon there will be about 80 more.
Negotiations on the construction of the gas station network are also underway with other regions.
According to the director of the department "Rossettey" Vladimir Sofiin, the company believes in the market of electric vehicles and is ready to build filling stations throughout the country, but there are also problems: a small number of electric vehicles in the country and the lack of a uniform standard for charging electric vehicles of different brands.
In addition, Rossetti, as a network company, does not have the right to sell electricity, the possibility of doing so with regard to charging electric vehicles is being explored.
Pankov believes that the most effective measure of state support for the formation of the Russian electric car market is zeroing customs duties.
The zero rate will be valid until the end of 2014, the possibility of its extension, extension of the preferential list is under consideration.
Replacing the transport tax with an environmental tax (the idea is discussed and concerns all machines) will also support the market, but not as tangible as customs preferences, according to Pankov.
Transport tax in Russia is low, says Pankov, unlike Norway, where the tax cut has led to a sharp increase in sales of electric cars - now they account for 12% of the market.
In Russia, stimulating measures for car owners are also needed, for example, free parking in the city center (as already done in Moscow), Pankov is sure, or the possibility of moving electric vehicles on designated lanes, which in Russia is not yet.
